Wardens are defensive melee fighters descended from the road warden companies of the Keeper Era.
They were professional escorts chartered to protect caravans across the desert road network.
Core doctrine: holding assigned ground. Patience under pressure, positional awareness, and capacity to absorb damage without breaking.
Combat role is frontline tank and protector with sustained defensive capability.
The foundational engagement is the Forty-Three Days at the Seven Shade Arches, where Warden-Sergeant Dunmar held a waystation through pure defensive discipline.
Ember Warden combat doctrine: fight near infrastructure, target logistics, hold until the objective is secured.
After the Ninth Meridian charter system collapsed, the most cohesive companies reorganized as the Reaver Confederates and became the first civic militias.
Two schools define the modern tradition: Dunmar School (discipline supersedes orders) and Registry School (institutional obedience provides legitimacy).
The Knight tradition descended from and formalized warden doctrine during the Iron Reformation.
